{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"4671005b-cb66-4a22-882c-96994134619d","content":"Yes, you'll hit **compatibility issues** with your target frameworks. MSTest v3 dropped support for:\n\n- **`net5.0`** — .NET 5 is no longer supported; you need **.NET 6+**\n- **`net462`** — .NET Framework older than 4.6.2 is borderline, but `net462` itself is the minimum. This one should still work.\n- **`netcoreapp3.1`** — .NET Core 3.1 is **dropped**; you need .NET 6+\n\nSo two of your three targets (`net5.0` and `netcoreapp3.1`) are incompatible with MSTest v3.\n\n### To migrate, you'd need to update `TargetFrameworks` to something like:\n\n```\nnet6.0;net462\n```\n\nor `net8.0;net462` depending on what you need to support.\n\nWould you like me to invoke the full MSTest v2→v3 migration skill to walk through all the changes (assertions, `DataRow`, timeouts, etc.) and update your project?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"75a50af3-f0d3-4ad0-b032-8f4de27a7482","outputTokens":255,"requestId":"BC27:A067E:1FD02E1:23A240D:69FAA88C"},"id":"cc7fefa4-7f7b-4cd4-8915-55132d491395","timestamp":"2026-05-06T02:33:56.367Z","parentId":"bf109aff-c66d-40fa-a122-6fd3e5d929dc"}
